UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2367
1 AN ACT relating to pedestrian swinging bridges.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 67.083 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) It is the purpose of this section to provide counties as units of general purpose local
5 government with the necessary latitude and flexibility to provide and finance
6 various governmental services within those functional areas specified in subsection
7 (3) of this section, while the General Assembly retains full authority to prescribe
8 and limit by statute local governmental activities when it deems the[such] action
9 necessary.
10 (2) The fiscal court of any county is hereby authorized to levy all taxes not in conflict
11 with the Constitution and statutes of this Commonwealth[state] now or hereafter
12 enacted.
13 (3) The fiscal court shall have the power to carry out governmental functions necessary
14 for the operation of the county. Except as otherwise provided by statute or the
15 Kentucky Constitution, the fiscal court of any county may enact ordinances, issue
16 regulations, levy taxes, issue bonds, appropriate funds, and employ personnel in
17 performance of the following public functions:
18 (a) Control of animals[,] and abatement of public nuisances;
19 (b) Regulation of public gatherings;
20 (c) Public sanitation and vector control;
21 (d) Provision of hospitals, ambulance service, programs for the health and welfare
22 of the aging and juveniles, and other public health facilities and services;
23 (e) Provision of corrections facilities and services, and programs for the
24 confinement, care, and rehabilitation of juvenile law offenders;
25 (f) Provision of parks, nature preserves, swimming pools, recreation areas,
26 libraries, museums, and other recreational and cultural facilities and
27 programs;
