1 (g) Provision of cemeteries and memorials;
2 (h) Conservation, preservation, and enhancement of natural resources including
3 soils, water, air, vegetation, and wildlife;
4 (i) Control of floods;
5 (j) Facilitating the construction and purchase of new and existing housing;
6 causing the repair or demolition of structures which present a hazard to public
7 health, safety, or morals or are otherwise inimical to the welfare of residents
8 of the county; causing the redevelopment of housing and related commercial,
9 industrial, and service facilities in urban or rural areas; providing education
10 and counseling services and technical assistance to present and future
11 residents of publicly assisted housing;
12 (k) Planning, zoning, and subdivision control according to the provisions of KRS
13 Chapter 100;
14 (l) Adoption, by reference or in full, of technical codes governing new
15 construction, renovation, or maintenance of structures intended for human
16 occupancy;
17 (m) Regulation of commerce for the protection and convenience of the public;
18 (n) Regulation of the sale of alcoholic beverages according to the provisions of
19 KRS Chapters 241 to 244;
20 (o) Exclusive management of solid wastes by ordinance,[ or] contract, or[ by]
21 both and disposition of abandoned vehicles;
22 (p) Provision of public buildings, including armories, necessary for the effective
23 delivery of public services;
24 (q) Cooperation with other units of government and private agencies for the
25 provision of public services, including[,] but not limited to[,] training,
26 educational services, and cooperative extension service programs;
27 (r) Provision of water,[ and] sewage, and garbage disposal service but not gas or
